Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle of a Corcyrean pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '576'. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 110, 12. Name Agathinos. Very close to Athenian Agora SS11825, whose handle shape is also similar to this amydaloid shape. Virginia Grace noted 'Corcyraean?'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1256)
